{%- comment -%}
  LimeSpot "ghost" placeholder for the preview theme.

  PROBLEM: LimeSpot's SDK loads on the preview theme (we see
  window.LimeSpot fully populated with .runtime / .Recommendations /
  .Storefront), but its admin-side "widget locations" config doesn't
  include unpublished themes — so the SDK never injects DOM widgets on
  this preview. Reviewers see no green boxes.

  SOLUTION: render lightweight green-bordered ghost placeholders in the
  same logical positions where LimeSpot CURRENTLY renders on the live
  Pipeline 6 theme (per LimeSpot's PageInfo configuration). These let
  the team see "this is where LimeSpot is today vs where Vertex would
  go" inside ONE preview, no live-vs-preview tab-switching.

  Each ghost is clearly labeled "[LimeSpot ghost — actually renders on
  live]" so no one mistakes it for a real widget.

  Usage:
    {% render 'limespot-ghost-placeholder',
        placement: 'pdp_below_description',
        title: 'You may also like'
    %}

  Same toolbar toggle controls visibility (vertex-preview-mode--vertex
  hides these; vertex-preview-mode--limespot hides Vertex).
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- assign placement = placement | default: 'unknown' -%}
{%- assign rec_title = title | default: 'You may also like' -%}
{%- comment -%}
  revenue_per_wk_php (number) — when set and > 0, renders an "active
  LimeSpot position" note showing the weekly attribution from the
  LimeSpot admin dashboard. When unset/0, renders the "$0 gap" note.
  Lets the same snippet handle both replacement positions and net-new
  positions with appropriate framing.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign rev_php = revenue_per_wk_php | default: 0 -%}

<div class="limespot-ghost-slot" data-limespot-placement="{{ placement }}">
  <div class="limespot-ghost-slot__header">
    <span class="limespot-ghost-slot__badge">LIMESPOT</span>
    <span class="limespot-ghost-slot__title">{{ rec_title }}</span>
    <span class="limespot-ghost-slot__placement-label">{{ placement | replace: '_', ' ' }}</span>
  </div>
  <div class="limespot-ghost-slot__note">
    {%- if rev_php > 0 -%}
      <strong>LimeSpot earns ~₱{{ rev_php }}/wk here</strong> — replacement
      target. Per LimeSpot's admin dashboard, this page type currently
      contributes the listed attribution. Vertex would compete directly
      for this revenue. (Real LimeSpot DOM doesn't render on this preview
      theme — their admin's widget-locations config only activates on the
      published theme; this ghost stands in for it visually.)
    {%- else -%}
      <strong>LimeSpot earns ₱0 here today</strong> — opportunity gap. Per
      LimeSpot's own admin dashboard, this page type currently contributes
      ₱0 to attributed revenue. Vertex's research-backed placement at this
      position is a net-new revenue play, not a replacement.
    {%- endif -%}
  </div>
  <div class="limespot-ghost-slot__grid">
    {%- for col in collections -%}
      {%- if col.products.size >= 4 -%}
        {%- for rp in col.products limit: 4 -%}
          <div class="limespot-ghost-slot__card">
            {%- if rp.featured_image -%}
              <img
                class="limespot-ghost-slot__img"
                src="{{ rp.featured_image | image_url: width: 200 }}"
                alt="{{ rp.title | escape }}"
                loading="lazy"
                width="100" height="100"
              >
            {%- endif -%}
            <div class="limespot-ghost-slot__card-title">{{ rp.title | truncate: 50 }}</div>
            <div class="limespot-ghost-slot__card-price">{{ rp.price | money }}</div>
          </div>
        {%- endfor -%}
        {%- break -%}
      {%- endif -%}
    {%- endfor -%}
  </div>
</div>
